Currently Hibernate doesn&#39;t know how to map your entities. You have 2 options here to use mappedBy from `Question` (OneToMany side) or to use `@JoinColumn` from Answer(ManyToOneSide). Here you can check an article https://www.baeldung.com/jpa-joincolumn-vs-mappedby about that.

Also if you want to save them from `Question` side you can used `cascadeType` and `orphanRemoval`. If you want to check more information about them - here is another article https://vladmihalcea.com/the-best-way-to-map-a-onetomany-association-with-jpa-and-hibernate/ .

If you want your code to work just add this annotation above your `Question` code:

    @OneToMany(
        mappedBy = &quot;question&quot;,
        cascade = CascadeType.ALL,
        orphanRemoval = true
    )
    private List&lt;Answer&gt; answers;

