Basically you reserve, increase `filled`, also for non-leafs.

    int leafToArray(Node n, int[] a, int filled){
        if (n == null) {
            return filled;
        }
        filled = leafToArray(n.left, a, filled);

        if (n.left == null &amp;&amp; n.right == null) {
            a[filled] = n.key;
            ++filled;
        }
        return leafToArray(n.right, a, filled);
    }

The problem is that the running index, `filled`, must be both input parameter and result. It can be done differently, but this is fine.

Do not introduce too many variables, they complicate things here.

